{{lead too short|date=December 2017}} {{update|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox orchestra |name = ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra |image = ABSCBNOrchestra.svg |location = [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] |founded = {{start date and age|2012|7|20}} |music_director = [[Gerard Salonga]] |website = {{url|philharmonic.abs-cbn.com}} }}
The '''ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra''' is a Filipino orchestra based in Manila. It was founded in 2012 with financial support from [[ABS-CBN]] and [[First Philippine Holdings Corporation|First Philippine Holdings]]. It is composed of 40 instrumentalists.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andoque|first=[[Neil Jason]]|title=ABS-CBN Philharmonic performs for Kapamilyas|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/07/03/12/abs-cbn-philharmonic-performs-kapamilyas|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref><ref name="Debut">{{cite web|last=Hila|first=Antonio C.|title=ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra to hold inaugural concert Aug. 18|url=http://lifestyle.inquirer.net/59751/abs-cbn-philharmonic-orchestra-to-hold-inaugural-concert-aug-18|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=28 August 2012|date=30 July 2012}}</ref> The orchestra's musical director and conductor is [[Gerard Salonga]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Ching|first=Mark Angelo|title=ABS-CBN forms its own philharmonic orchestra|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/35007/abs-cbn-forms-its-own-philharmonic-orchestra/1/2|work=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|accessdate=28 August 2012|date=24 July 2012}}</ref>
== History == The official debut of ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra was on July 20, 2012 in a concert held at the [[Dolphy theater]]. The orchestra played some classical pieces and some musical score of Filipino films.<ref name="Debut"/> Its first major public debut was on the "Icons at the Arena” concert at the [[SM Mall of Asia Arena]] on July 16, 2012. The orchestra played some of the most recognized film scores of the American composer [[John Williams]] in its first solo concert, "The Magic of John Williams" on September 2, 2012 at the [[Meralco Theater]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra celebrates John Williams and the magic of his music!|url=http://rodmagaru.com/2012/08/17/music-abs-cbn-philharmonic-orchestra-celebrates-john-williams-magic-music/|work=Rod Magaru Show|accessdate=28 August 2012|date=17 August 2012}}</ref> In 2013, due to public demand, the orchestra repeated their concert "The Magic of John Williams" on February 23 held also at the Meralco Theatre.<ref>{{cite web|title=ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra to do a repeat of ‘The Magic of John Williams’|url=http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/12862/ABS-CBN-Philharmonic-Orchestra-to-do-a-repeat-of-The-Magic-of-John-Williams-.aspx|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]]|accessdate=21 February 2013|date=24 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Tanchanco|first=John Paul|title=Hollywood maestro featured in Philharmonic concert|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/01/23/13/hollywood-maestro-featured-philharmonic-concert|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|accessdate=21 February 2013|date=24 January 2013}}</ref> The orchestra has played alongside [[Andrea Bocelli]], [[Idina Menzel]], [[Lea Salonga]], [[Lisa Macuja-Elizalde|Lisa Macuja]], [[Ballet Philippines]], [[Ballet Manila]], [[Joanna Ampil]], [[Jose Mari Chan]], [[Ogie Alcasid]], [[Martin Nievera]], [[Pilita Corrales]], [[Louie Ocampo]], [[Ryan Cayabyab]], [[Basil Valdez]], [[Rey Valera]], [[Christian Bautista]], [[Janella Salvador]], [[Jona Viray|Jona]], and [[Xian Lim]] among many others.
==Film scores== ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra has scored several films including ''Debosyon'' (2013), ''[[Ignacio de Loyola]]'' (2016), and ''[[Ang Larawan]]'' (2017). The orchestra also provided the musical score for the [[Agila: The EKsperience]] attraction of [[Enchanted Kingdom]].
