'''Marian Ulc''' (born Szałas, Poland, 1947) – a [[Poland|Polish]] sculptor, representing the [[naive art]] movement. His works have been displayed outside [[Poland]], for example in [[Germany]] and [[Sweden]]. He is most famously known for his 1968 work, "The Greatest Zanzibar Man of Cratus", and his 1971 work, "Bouncing Black Babies". To This day, it is unknown whether he lived or died.

