'''Melissa Johns''' is a British actor and disability ambassador. She was born  without right forearm and hand.<ref>{{cite web |title=Melissa Johns |url=https://www.spotlight.com/interactive/cv/3416-7869-5989 |website=Spotlight.com |publisher=[[Spotlight (company)]] |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> She played [[Imogen Pascoe]] in ''[[Coronation Street]]'' in 2017. On 6 November 2018, it was confirmed that Johns will be returning to ''Coronation Street'', with her return being aired in December.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/11/06/coronation-street-spoilers-melissa-johns-returns-as-kates-ex-imogen-for-rana-reunion-storyline-8110268/|title=Coronation Street spoilers: Melissa Johns returns as Kate's ex Imogen for Rana reunion storyline|last1=Lindsay |first1=Duncan|date=6 November 2018|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|accessdate=6 November 2018 }}</ref> 

In 2018, her smartphone was hacked and intimate photos were released.<ref name="bbc">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/42779958/ex-corrie-actress-turns-sex-photo-hack-into-positive-thing|title=Ex-Corrie actress turns sex photo hack into 'positive thing' - BBC Newsbeat|website=bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2018-01-25}}</ref> The experience inspired the [[BBC Radio 4]] drama ''In My Own Skin'', written by Debbie Oates with Johns, and starring Johns.<ref>{{cite web |title=In My Own Skin |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0000xxg |website=Bbc.co.uk |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>

