[[Image:Followspot operator.jpg|thumb|right|A spotlight operator working]] The '''Spotlight operator''' or '''Followspot Operator''', is a [[theatrical technician]] who operates a specialized [[stage lighting instrument]] known as a [[followspot]]. A followspot is any lighting instrument manually controlled by an operator during a performance. Generally a followspot will be a dedicated, large lighting instrument designed to pan, change size, beam width, and color easily by hand.
==Followspot controls== *Choppers – Cuts or shutters the top and bottom part of the beam. *Douser – Controls intensity. *Iris – Controls beam size. *Trombone – Controls focal length. *Color Frames – Changes the color of the light. May also known as a boomerang and/or a [[color magazine (lighting)|color magazine]]. Color magazines contain the [[color gel]]s, which are counted from the rear of the follow spot forward.
==See also== * [[Stage lighting]] * [[Stage lighting instrument]] * [[Light board operator]] * [[Electrician (theater)#Deck Electrician|Deck Electrician]] * [[Super Trouper (spotlight)|Super Trouper]]
